@PressTV

Major World Events by Morning of February 25 

🟠Zimbabwe has suspended exports ⁠of all raw minerals and lithium concentrates with immediate effect, the minister of mines announced;

🟠ECOWAS Chiefs of Staff have reportedly gathered in Freetown, Sierra Leone, for a three-day meeting to discuss the future of the regional Standby Force and its role in countering terrorism in West Africa;

🟠Togo proposes establishing an African New Year, arguing that colonial policies distorted African identity—including the imposition of a foreign calendar, the country's foreign ministry stated;

🟠Israeli President Isaac Herzog arrived in Ethiopia on Wednesday morning for an official visit, with meetings scheduled with Ethiopia's leadership, his office said;

🟠China opposes any proliferation or use of nuclear weapons, including a potential Western transfer of such arms to Ukraine, Foreign Ministry spokesperson Mao Ning stated;

🟠Tehran dismissed US statements about Iran's missiles, nuclear program, and unrest casualties as false, Iran’s Foreign Ministry spokesman said, following Trump's remarks, that the US has not yet “heard” Iran renounce nuclear weapons.

